  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary disease (COPD) patients with chronic hypercapnic respiratory
      failure are more likely to develop exacerbations. Non-invasive ventilation has been proposed
      to treat acute respiratory failure but little information is available about the benefits of
      home non-invasive ventilation in COPD patients with chronic hypercapnic respiratory failure
      surviving an acute hypercapnic respiratory failure. The purpose of this study is to determine
      whether home non-invasive ventilation can reduce recurrent acute hypercapnic respiratory
      failure in COPD patients who survived an episode of acute hypoxemic respiratory failure
      (AHRF) treated by Non-invasive ventilation (NIV).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
